      • addProviderFinders

        protected void addProviderFinders(ProviderFinder... providerFinders)
        Add ProviderFinder to the graph directly. Eg. if manual provider registration is needed, a ProviderFinderByRegistry can be added.

        Note that, when there are multiple ProviderFinders able to inject an instance the later merged graph wins.

        Parameters:
        providerFinders - The ProviderFinders to add

      • get

        public <T> T get(java.lang.Class<T> type,
        java.lang.annotation.Annotation qualifier,
        java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> injectAnnotation)
      throws ProviderMissingException,
             ProvideException,
             CircularDependenciesException
        Get an instance matching the type and qualifier. If there is an instance cached, the cached instance will be returned otherwise a new instance will be created.

        Note that, not like inject(Object, Class) this method will NOT increment reference count for the injectable object with the same type and qualifier.

        Parameters:
        type - the type of the object
        qualifier - the qualifier of the injected object. Null is allowed if no qualifier is specified
        Returns:
        The cached object or a new instance matching the type and qualifier
        Throws:
        ProviderMissingException - throw if the provider matching the requiredType and qualifier is not found
        ProvideException - throw when failed to create a new instance
        CircularDependenciesException - throw when circular dependency found during injecting the newly created instance

      • release

        public void release(java.lang.Object target,
           java.lang.Class<? extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> injectAnnotation)
             throws ProviderMissingException
        Release cached instances held by fields of target object. References of cache of the instances will be decremented. Once the reference count of a controller reaches 0, it will be removed from the cache and raise Provider.OnFreedListener.
        Parameters:
        target - Whose fields will be injected
        injectAnnotation - Annotated which a field will be recognize
        Throws:
        ProviderMissingException
